3 fisher test

# set MYB pos/neg
opscc_hpvPos$MYB_status = FetchData(object = opscc_hpvPos,vars = "MYB") %>%
  mutate(MYB_status = if_else(
    condition = MYB> 0,
    true = "MYB+",
    false = "MYB-"
  )) %>% 
  pull(MYB_status)

#set HPV to consider + if hpv_score>3
opscc_hpvPos$hpv = FetchData(object = opscc_hpvPos,vars = "hpv") %>%
 mutate(hpv = if_else(condition = hpv_score>=3,true = "HPV+",false = "HPV-")) %>% 
  pull(hpv)



library(rstatix)
myplots <- list()  # new empty list


for (patient_name in unique(opscc_hpvPos$patient) %>%  base::setdiff("OP13")) { #OP13 has no MYB+ cells
  patient_data = subset(x = opscc_hpvPos, subset = patient == patient_name)
  df  = FetchData(object = patient_data,
                  vars = c("hpv", "MYB_status","hpv_score"))  %>%
   
    select(-hpv_score) %>% 
    droplevels()
  test = fisher_test(table(df))
  p = ggbarstats(
    df,
    MYB_status,
    hpv,
    results.subtitle = FALSE,
    subtitle = paste0("Fisher's exact test", ", p-value = ",
                      test$p)
  ,title = patient_name)
  myplots[[patient_name]] <- p  # add each plot into plot list

}
ggarrange(plotlist = myplots,common.legend = T)

3.1 Samples average

total_cells_df  = FetchData(object = opscc_hpvPos, vars = c("patient")) %>% dplyr::count(patient, name = "total_cells")
df  = FetchData(object = opscc_hpvPos,
                vars = c("hpv", "MYB_status", "hpv_score", "patient")) %>%
  select(-hpv_score) %>%
  group_by(patient,MYB_status) %>%
  dplyr::count(hpv) %>%
  left_join(total_cells_df, by = "patient") %>% 
  mutate(relative_n = round((n/total_cells)*1000,digits = 0)) %>% 
  group_by(MYB_status,hpv) %>% 
  summarise(total_relative_n = sum(relative_n)) %>% 
  droplevels()
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'MYB_status'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
df_wide = 
  df %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = hpv, values_from = total_relative_n) %>%
  column_to_rownames("MYB_status") 
    
  test = fisher_test(df_wide)
  p = ggbarstats(
    df,
    MYB_status,
    hpv,
    counts = total_relative_n,
    results.subtitle = FALSE,
    # subtitle = paste0("Fisher's exact test", ", p-value = ", test$p) # depends in the normalized amount o
  ,title = "OPSCC")
p

4 MYB targets

# load MYB targets
library("readxl")
myb_tergets <- read_excel("./Input_data/MYB_tergets_PMC4767593_sup_table_4.xlsx",col_names = T) %>% pull(Gene)
# add score
myb_tergets_score = FetchData(object = opscc_hpvPos,vars = myb_tergets,slot = "data") %>% rowMeans()
myb_tergets_df = data.frame(myb_tergets_score,row.names = names(myb_tergets_score))
opscc_hpvPos = AddMetaData(object = opscc_hpvPos,metadata = myb_tergets_df)
genes_by_tp = FetchData(object = opscc_hpvPos,vars = c("hpv", "myb_tergets_score","hpv_score","patient"),slot = "data")  %>% 
  mutate(hpv = if_else(condition = hpv_score>=3,true = "HPV+",false = "HPV-")) 


# all cells by patient boxplot
formula <- as.formula("myb_tergets_score ~ hpv")

#plot and split by patient:
stat.test <- genes_by_tp %>%
  group_by(patient) %>%
  t_test(formula) %>%
  adjust_pvalue(method = "fdr") %>%
  add_significance() %>%
  add_xy_position(x = "hpv") %>%
  mutate(p.adj = signif(p.adj, digits = 2))
stat.test


plt = ggplot(genes_by_tp, aes(x = hpv, y = myb_tergets_score)) +
  geom_violin(scale = "width",aes(fill = hpv)) +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.2, outlier.shape = NA) +
  facet_wrap( ~ patient, scales = "free") +
  stat_pvalue_manual(stat.test, label = "{p.adj}")  + #add p value
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0.05, 0.2))) + # Add 10% spaces between the p-value labels and the plot border
  ggtitle("MYB targets")
plt
